The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of deep learning models for face recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with image processing and analysis, which can be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of preprocessing on the performance of deep learning models, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
